s/music/picture-parlour-join-great-escape-boycott-promise-fundraising-gig-for-palestinian-relief-3756565">Picture Parlor</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/alfie-templeman">Alfie Templeman</a> 。</p><p>其他人， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-big-special-explain-why-theyre-playing-the-great-escape-amidst-the-boycott-and-donating-fee-to-palestinian-charity-3756668">如 Big Special</a> ，参加了比赛，但将其费用捐赠给了巴勒斯坦慈善机构，而<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/kneecap-explain-their-decision-to-play-the-great-escape-over-boycott-you-cant-de-platform-yourself-3763758">Kneecap 参加了比赛，但始终表示对巴勒斯坦的支持</a>。成员莫格莱·巴普 (Móglai Bap) <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/the-cover/the-cover-kneecap-interview-fine-art-3761722">6 月份告诉<em>《NME》</em></a> ，“如果你的收入依赖于今生，而且你是一支巡演乐队，那么一切都以某种方式与这些公司之一相关联。理想情况下，如果我们有钱，我们就会抵制一切，坐在家里整天发推文。”</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/joe-the-shitboys-accuse-the-great-escape-of-ethnocentric-bullying-for-dropping-the-faroe-islands-as-country-partner-3797109">《Joe &amp; The Shitboys》指责 The Great Escape 放弃法罗群岛作为国家合作伙伴是“种族中心主义欺凌”，</a>该帖子首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
